caption: Great entrees (Szechuan Spicy Fish!). Great value. Sushi is sneaky good. Delicious spot. Coming back soon and often. Best of all, the people at Lotus are genuine, good people. Couldn't ask for more.

I stopped by on a whim to grab a nosh for the cold walk home.  I got the most BEAUTIFUL spring rolls I have ever had.  They looked like a food magazine photo shoot...the fake food thats not real???  Well they were real.  And delicious!  The dipping sauce was just as exciting.  But the best part for me was the milk tea with bubbles... My partner and I are new to the area and just mentioned how excited I was to have a place close to home where I could run over to anytime and grab one. The man who was working must have heard us because he brought me one out while we waited.  YUM YUM YUM 😋  It was so kind.  I don't run into that all that often so that will bring me back alone! I am excited to try different things on the menu.  It was great food, a friendly atmosphere and an all around excellent experience!
Very underwhelming. Gao's chicken had no flavor, sushi was middle of the road at best, dumplings tasted like burnt tortilla
Ok. Food not greases.
Good food just expensive

Had delivery from Lotus Express tonight.  It arrived 5 minutes earlier than expected,  was piping hot and delicious.  I had the appetizers sampler and crispy seasame orange chicken.  I would strongly suggest considering them for your next Chinese food delivery.
You can order stuff not on the menu...they know how to make Xinjiang dishes. Try ordering the cumin lo mein or chong qing chicken...you won't regret it.
Wow absolutely amazing food here, best all around.I been to so many restaurants and this is far the best for Chinese food. Alan is great.
Great portions and delicious food !!!!

I ordered from here for the first time tonight and have never been more disappointed with chinese food in my life. Their photos look great and their reviews make their food seem great. I ordered sweet and sour chicken with rice and spring rolls. What I received was chicken fingers with a side of sweet and sour sauce, plain brown rice, and a single spring roll.
Great food
It’s cheap, it’s edible, and they are fast. Perfect local spot.
Delightful food. Chicken that actually looks like chicken. They've always been quick as well.

I'm afraid the food was not my taste. I ordered Chicken Teriyaki and Avocado Salad via Uber Eats but the package was leaking and the tray itself was oily. I guess some people would like it, but to me Chicken Teriyaki was like the one from a very cheap Chinese restaurant (it only contains oily chicken and broccoli). Avocado Salad was weirdly lukewarm and didn't feel fresh...I would rather cook myself

This is the best Asian place ever. You can never go wrong. Sushi combos, pad Thai, miso soup are some of my favorite. I’m sad to be moving away from Lotus but glad they were able to open back up again (due to COVID-19) before I left. Thanks for the great service!
The schezwan beef is pretty good
1st time here. It was good! Not salty in any way. The spicy tuna roll was delish! Not too hot, very flavorful.
Don't be misled by the fast food decorum.  The proprietor comes from a family line of high-end Asian restaurant businesses, and the food is of corresponding taste and quality.

This food was so great, and it was ready in less than the time it took me to get there.  The spicy beef is up there with my favorite Sichuan cuisine.
The food is really good, and the staff are friendly. However, the only thing keeping me from giving 5 stars is that it took over an hour to have my food delivered to me.

Great food, fast and nice staff.  I come here once a month or so, maybe a bit more but today was the first day I met Danny, just wanted to say he's killing it! He was very aware of what was happening in the restaurant, kept on top of things and was cleaning up in the downtime. Very courteous as well. I wish I had been carrying cash to leave a tip, next time!

Finally stopped here last week after driving by so many times. Wished i had stopped earlier. Most helpful person behind the counter answering my questions and expaining the menu. Got the salmon poke as takeout and enjoyed it immensely. Cannot wait to go back and start working my way thru the menu. Next to try: Chow Foon noodles.

This is our neighborhood Asian fusion place and I've been here twice before with good experience. Today I got a pad thai and it came swimming in a pool of liquid. Pad thai is stir fried noodles and should not be soupy. The place also seemed to be run by loud, raucous teenagers. It felt generally disorganized and unpleasant to sit down and have dinner. Hopefully this was just a rare occurrence and my bad luck. I do like this place and would come back again.

Food is good and good prices, the people at the front taking your order are a little awkward but besides that not bad at all, I usually pick this place if I want a good portion of Chinese food that wont make me sick !

Good place to eat Chinese food but if you are craving chicken wings you won’t find them here, the fried rice is very good I had a sampler platter witch was good but I would’ve preferred chicken wings instead of chicken fingers as one of the choices. Also this place is a little more expensive than your average Chinese restaurant, that being said I would definitely recommend it.

The Poke bowl is quite good. We got the tuna and salmon combo, and the fish tasted fresh and the wonton crisps added a nice crunch. The poke sauce was also creamy and slightly citrusy, another nice touch. The hot and sour soup was also one of the better ones I've had. I would go back to the restaurant because of the friendly servers and food, but it's definitely pricey for the amount of food and the fast food-like atmosphere.

I enjoyed the Mongolian beef and a few other dishes.  The staff are very friendly and the wait time is minimal.   The restaurant is on the smaller scale but there was plenty of room when I ate there.  The cleanliness and decor is well above typical Chinese restaurants.

I absolutely love this restaurant. The delivery is always early and if you decide to eat at the restaurant, the food comes out very quickly.

This place is okay. The staff is friendly, and there is not much of a waiting time involved; but the food itself is not very impressive. I have tried about three dishes here so far - mala spicy vegetables with fried tofu, vegetarian delight and General Gao's chicken. The veggie dishes were not as flavorful, but the spring rolls are pretty good. Overall, a mediocre place to get a lunch combo under $10.

Absolutely delicious. Happened upon it when I went to my eye appointment. I got the General Gao's Chicken and crab Rangoon. Not too pricey. Great value and impressive delivery.

Not bad, not bad at all. Place is small. Better for takeout. Workers have that "Hurry up and buy." attitude but they are polite. My suggestion is to call ahead your order better than wait there.

The Red Thai Curry is excellent and packs a kick! Also, the plating is unbelievably nice and the location is extremely pleasant. Sidenote: The tofu is not a firm or extra firm variety, but it's still extremely tasty.

Going somewhere new and clean for Chinese food is always a nice change of pace. You actually would want to sit down and eat inside of Lotus Xpress instead of running away with your takeout order as fast as possible. Really nice and relatively speedy service too.
